description: Retrieves information about objects that Amazon Macie selected from an S3 bucket for automated sensitive data discovery.

parameters.name: resourceArn
parameters.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the S3 bucket that the request applies to.

nested_items.name: artifacts
nested_items.description: An array of objects, one for each of 1-100 S3 objects that Amazon Macie selected for analysis.

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the object.

nested_items.name: classificationResultStatus
nested_items.description: The status of the analysis. Possible values are:
COMPLETE - Amazon Macie successfully completed its analysis of the object.
PARTIAL - Macie analyzed only a subset of data in the object. For example, the object is an archive file that contains files in an unsupported format.
SKIPPED - Macie wasn't able to analyze the object. For example, the object is a malformed file.

nested_items.name: sensitive
nested_items.description: Specifies whether Amazon Macie found sensitive data in the object.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: The string to use in a subsequent request to get the next page of results in a paginated response. This value is null if there are no additional pages.
